.TH LPF-CHECK 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-check \- parse and validate policy without touching the host
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf check <policy>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Parse, type\-check, and validate an lpf policy without changing host state.
Diagnostics must include source locations and actionable recovery guidance.
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf check /etc/lpf.conf
lpf check fixtures/policies/basic.lpf
.SH FILES
/etc/lpf.conf
.SH SAFETY NOTES
This command is read\-only.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-plan(8), lpf\-fmt(8), lpf.conf(5)
